This paper is primarily focused on image enhancement using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a CNN for implementing a learned no-reference image quality metric suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper's focus on optimizing for perceptual quality suggests that it may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
